<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">clarrissa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I began this but have returned to Katta twice to try to do second part and NPC is not in room described.<P>Just wondering if there is camp/spawn time  something I am missing.  Any information would be appreciated<P>Be well<P>------------------<BR>Clarrisa<BR>51st Season Vicar<P>What lies behind and before us are tiny compared to what lies within us</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry, I did this quest like a week after SoL came out and am like ten quests distant from it-LOL.<P>What part exactly are you asking about? A few details to jar my memory and I'm sure I can help you out with timers/locations and the like.<P>I really liked this quest-I'll be getting rid of the cloak as soon as I finsh my Shield of Bane Warding since the +5% med can't take me above 252-but the quest itself was a hell of alot of fun =)<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 53rd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kessina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Let's see<P>part 1 = holy water thing<BR>Take the holy water and "pour" it on the guy in the cathedral.<P>part 2 = diary<BR>Have a rogue pick the locked door in Nathyn's(sp?) building 2nd floor, pick up book on the desk.<P>part 3 = peqi<BR>Kill Peqi in haven.<P>part 4 = Akheva no rent loot<P>part 5 = kill arbogast and miller<P>Is that the 2nd part you are referring to?  Who's missing? If arbogast and miller is missing in the bar in lower Katta, they probably got killed by someone who were doing part 5 and haven't respawn.  I don't have a timer on their spawn though.  Other than that, you don't need to talk to anyone in part 2.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Kessina Terok - 56 Templar of Tunare - The Hand - Xev Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kanbyen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">arbogast and miller are not up a lot of times.   They need to be killed to complete quest, so hence they die about the same speed as peqi spawns.  <P>Before You worry about arbogast and miller, try binding in the Peqi's room.  Check him every day, till you get that part, its the real bottle neck to this quest.  Once you get it, work on the others. <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Docter Stormfist</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How I camped Peqi in Shadow Haven...<P>Sat down in his spawn location, put speakers next to pillow, cranked them up, went to sleep, 2 hours later when he spawned in, he buffed himself...needless to say I jumped up out of bed, grabbed the nearest tank (54 SK troll friend of mine) and took the gnome down.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ragefire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">is picking the lock the only way to get the stuff out of 'nathyn Illuminious' locked room?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Azhure_Sunsoar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yep, need a rogue there to pick the lock, beware the servant, think there's a trap there in the room, keeps casting colour flux/stun.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ragefire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">so when i open the room i should expect a fight?<BR>how people do i need?<P>i am lvl 55 cleric (not much of a tank)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Azhure_Sunsoar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I went into room and picked up the book, coterie servant popped.<BR>I was lv 58 when I fought it, with a lv 55 rogue. He was pretty easy except the rogue got caught in the stun trap and couldn't attack. I did most the dmg, was down to 2 bubs of health, I had fear memmed, feared it.. and it ran out. I gated out not knowing what happened, so cleared aggro, ran back in zone to make sure the rogue was ok, and lo and behold the coterie servant was right outside Nathyn's place, he saw me and started to attack me hehe, but I don't think you need to fight it, unless you want xp  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Azhure</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ragefire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">now if i can just find a rogue - it has to be 201 lockpick still - correct?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kessina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You don't always have a fight in Nathlyn's room.  The pop is not triggered by the lock being picked or by the pickup of the book.  If you do it fast (pick lock, open door, run in, get book, leave, in say a few seconds), the coterie might not even spawn.<P>We did 3 books in a roll so we have to wait for the book to respawn.  We were trying to spawn the coterie with some consistency for xp, no luck.  If it was consistant and triggerable, that place would turn into an xp camp.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
